    "description": "The rabbit's foot fern (Davallia fejeensis) is an amazing species of fern which boasts beautiful furry fronds and furry rhizomes that are quite unique in the world of ferns. Its dark green fronds create an exotic and eye-catching display when grown in hanging baskets, adding lots of texture and movement to any room. This species is also great for purifying air and providing extra humidity to any space, and they are relatively low-maintenance and easy to take care of, making them an ideal choice for everyone from the average home gardener to experienced green-fingered enthusiasts.",
